#: ../../source/scenic_quality.rst:52
msgid "How it Works"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/scenic_quality.rst:53
msgid ""
"The InVEST scenic quality model computes the visual impact of features in"
" the landscape in several steps:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/scenic_quality.rst:55
msgid "For each structure site:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/scenic_quality.rst:57
msgid ""
"Calculate the visibility for each point feature *X* "
"(*intermediate\\\\visibility_X.tix*) based on the Wang et al reference-"
"plane viewshed algorithm."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/scenic_quality.rst:58
msgid ""
"From the visibility, determine the value of the visibility "
"amenity/disamenity by weighting the visibility and applying the valuation"
" function defined in the user interface (*intermediate\\\\value_X.tif*)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/scenic_quality.rst:60
msgid ""
"Sum the valuation rasters to create a weighted aggregate "
"(*output\\\\vshed_value.tif*)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/scenic_quality.rst:62
msgid ""
"Divide the weighted, aggregate valuation raster into quartiles to create "
"a raster representing visual quality (*output\\\\vshed_qual.tif*)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/scenic_quality.rst:64
msgid ""
"Weight and sum the visibility rasters from all structures points to "
"create a weighted sum of the number of visible points "
"(*output\\\\vshed.tif*)"
